h3cStorageMIB.name: h3cStorageMIB
h3cStorageMIB.contactinfo: Platform Team H3C Technologies Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China Http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
h3cStorageMIB.description: This MIB describes the general information of storage device, such as the property, configuration and management.

h3cRaidCapability.name: h3cRaidCapability
h3cRaidCapability.description: This object identifies if the agent support raid management.

h3cFcCapability.name: h3cFcCapability
h3cFcCapability.description: This object identifies if the agent support FC(fiber channel) management.

h3cNasCapability.name: h3cNasCapability
h3cNasCapability.description: This object identifies if the agent support NAS(Network Attached Storage).

h3cAdaptiveRepCapability.name: h3cAdaptiveRepCapability
h3cAdaptiveRepCapability.description: This object identifies if the agent support adaptive replication. With adaptive replication option, data from the primary resource is continuously replicated to a replication resource unless the system determines it is not practical or possible, such as when there is insufficient bandwidth. For continuous replication to occur, a continuous replication resource is used to stage the data being replicated from the primary resource. Similar to a cache, as soon as data comes into the continuous replication resource, it is written to the replication resource.

h3cRemoteRepCapability.name: h3cRemoteRepCapability
h3cRemoteRepCapability.description: This object identifies if the agent support remote replication.

h3cSafeCacheCapability.name: h3cSafeCacheCapability
h3cSafeCacheCapability.description: This object identifies if the agent support safe cache.

h3cSyncMirrorCapability.name: h3cSyncMirrorCapability
h3cSyncMirrorCapability.description: This object identifies if the agent support synchronized mirror.

h3cAsyncMirrorCapability.name: h3cAsyncMirrorCapability
h3cAsyncMirrorCapability.description: This object identifies if the agent support asynchronous mirror.

h3cTimeMarkCapability.name: h3cTimeMarkCapability
h3cTimeMarkCapability.description: This object identifies if the agent support time mark.

h3cSseCapability.name: h3cSseCapability
h3cSseCapability.description: This object identifies if the agent support SSE(Storage Service Enable).

h3ciSCSITargetEnable.name: h3ciSCSITargetEnable
h3ciSCSITargetEnable.description: This object identifies if the agent support iSCSI target.

h3cFcTargetEnable.name: h3cFcTargetEnable
h3cFcTargetEnable.description: This object identifies if the agent support FC target.

h3cServerLocationLedState.name: h3cServerLocationLedState
h3cServerLocationLedState.description: This object identifies the state of storage device's location led.

h3cServerResetButtonState.name: h3cServerResetButtonState
h3cServerResetButtonState.description: This object identifies if the reset button is enable.

h3cServerPowerButtonState.name: h3cServerPowerButtonState
h3cServerPowerButtonState.description: This object identifies if the power button is enable.

h3cServerPowerState.name: h3cServerPowerState
h3cServerPowerState.description: This object identifies the state of power supply in the server, and is valid when UPS has been configured successful. The value 'online' means power supply is well-balanced. The value 'onlinebypass' means supply power without ups. The value 'onbattery' means supply power with battery. The value 'unknown' means the power supply state is unknown.

h3cDeuTable.name: h3cDeuTable
h3cDeuTable.description: This table contains some information of a particular DEU(Disk Enclosure Unit).

h3cDeuEntry.name: h3cDeuEntry
h3cDeuEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a particular DEU.

h3cDeuIndex.name: h3cDeuIndex
h3cDeuIndex.description: This object identifies the index of h3cDeuTable. The DEU identified by a particular value of this index is the same object as identified by the same value of entPhysicalIndex.

h3cDeuIDLed.name: h3cDeuIDLed
h3cDeuIDLed.description: This object identifies the state of storage DEU's led.

h3cDeuDiskScan.name: h3cDeuDiskScan
h3cDeuDiskScan.description: The operation of scanning the table. When the value of this object is set to 'action', the operation of disk scanning is touched off.

h3cStorageInterfaceTable.name: h3cStorageInterfaceTable
h3cStorageInterfaceTable.description: This table describes the interface information of the network.

h3cStorageInterfaceEntry.name: h3cStorageInterfaceEntry
h3cStorageInterfaceEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a particular interface.

h3cStorageInterfaceIndex.name: h3cStorageInterfaceIndex
h3cStorageInterfaceIndex.description: This object identifies the index of H3cStorageInterfaceEntry. The interface identified by this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

h3cStorageInterfaceGateway.name: h3cStorageInterfaceGateway
h3cStorageInterfaceGateway.description: This object identifies the gateway address of interface.

h3cStorageInterfaceGatewayType.name: h3cStorageInterfaceGatewayType
h3cStorageInterfaceGatewayType.description: This object identifies the gateway address type of interface.

h3cStorageInterfaceMTU.name: h3cStorageInterfaceMTU
h3cStorageInterfaceMTU.description: This object identifies the MTU of interface.

h3cBondingTable.name: h3cBondingTable
h3cBondingTable.description: This table describes the information of the Bonding interface.

h3cBondingEntry.name: h3cBondingEntry
h3cBondingEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a particular Bonding interface.

h3cBondingIndex.name: h3cBondingIndex
h3cBondingIndex.description: This object identifies the index of h3cBondingEntry. The interface identified by this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

h3cBondingPortList.name: h3cBondingPortList
h3cBondingPortList.description: An entry contains management information applicable to a particular bonding interface. Every two bytes describe the ifIndex of an interface, and an interface belongs to one bonding group only. An interface should be deleted from the portlist of the bonding group it belongs to before it is added to another bonding group.

h3cScsiAdapterTable.name: h3cScsiAdapterTable
h3cScsiAdapterTable.description: This table containing some information of the SCSI(Small Computer System interface) adapter.

h3cScsiAdapterEntry.name: h3cScsiAdapterEntry
h3cScsiAdapterEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a particular SCSI adapter.

h3cAdapterNumber.name: h3cAdapterNumber
h3cAdapterNumber.description: This object identifies the index of the adapter .

h3cAdapterDesc.name: h3cAdapterDesc
h3cAdapterDesc.description: This object describes some information of the adapter.

h3cAdapterType.name: h3cAdapterType
h3cAdapterType.description: This object identifies the type of adapter. If the value of this object is not equal to 'fc', the associated object(such as h3cFcAdapterMode, h3cFcAdapterIWWPNs,h3cFcAdapterTWWPNs,h3cFcAdapterPortState,h3cFcAdapterModeSwitch) will be invalid.

h3cFcAdapterMode.name: h3cFcAdapterMode
h3cFcAdapterMode.description: This object identifies the mode type of adapter.

h3cFcAdapterInitiatorWwpnName.name: h3cFcAdapterInitiatorWwpnName
h3cFcAdapterInitiatorWwpnName.description: This object describes the FC's adapter WWPN(World Wide Port Name) numbers.

h3cFcAdapterTargetWwpnName.name: h3cFcAdapterTargetWwpnName
h3cFcAdapterTargetWwpnName.description: This object describes the FC's target WWPN numbers.

h3cFcAdapterPortState.name: h3cFcAdapterPortState
h3cFcAdapterPortState.description: This object identifies the state of adapter's interface.

h3cFcAdapterModeSwitch.name: h3cFcAdapterModeSwitch
h3cFcAdapterModeSwitch.description: This object identifies if the adapter work on a target mode.

h3cExtVoltageTable.name: h3cExtVoltageTable
h3cExtVoltageTable.description: This table contains some entity extend information of the voltage.

h3cExtVoltageEntry.name: h3cExtVoltageEntry
h3cExtVoltageEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to the voltage.

h3cExtVoltagePhysicalIndex.name: h3cExtVoltagePhysicalIndex
h3cExtVoltagePhysicalIndex.description: This object identifies the entity index of voltage.

h3cExtVoltagePhysicalName.name: h3cExtVoltagePhysicalName
h3cExtVoltagePhysicalName.description: This object identifies the entity name of voltage.

h3cExtVoltageLowThreshold.name: h3cExtVoltageLowThreshold
h3cExtVoltageLowThreshold.description: The low-threshold for the voltage. When voltage is lower than low-threshold, a notification will be sent.

h3cExtVoltageHighThreshold.name: h3cExtVoltageHighThreshold
h3cExtVoltageHighThreshold.description: The high-threshold for the voltage. When voltage is higher than high-threshold, a notification will be sent.

h3cExtCriticalVoltageLowThreshold.name: h3cExtCriticalVoltageLowThreshold
h3cExtCriticalVoltageLowThreshold.description: The critical low threshold for voltage. If the voltage is lower too much than the entity needs, the entity will halt.

h3cExtCriticalVoltageHighThreshold.name: h3cExtCriticalVoltageHighThreshold
h3cExtCriticalVoltageHighThreshold.description: The critical high threshold for voltage. If the voltage is higher too much than the entity needs, the entity will halt.

h3cExtShutdownVoltageLowThreshold.name: h3cExtShutdownVoltageLowThreshold
h3cExtShutdownVoltageLowThreshold.description: The voltage is lower than the critical low threshold. If the voltage is lower too much than the entity needs, the entity halts now.

h3cExtShutdownVoltageHighThreshold.name: h3cExtShutdownVoltageHighThreshold
h3cExtShutdownVoltageHighThreshold.description: The voltage is higher than the critical high threshold. If the voltage is higher too much than the entity needs, the entity halts now.

h3cSoftwareInfoString.name: h3cSoftwareInfoString
h3cSoftwareInfoString.description: This object identifies if the software's information.

h3cStorCriticalLowerTemperatureThreshold.name: h3cStorCriticalLowerTemperatureThresholdNotification
h3cStorCriticalLowerTemperatureThreshold.description: The h3cStorCriticalLowerTemperatureThresholdNotification indicates the temperature is lower than the threshold. If the temperature is lower too much than the entity needs, the entity will halt.

h3cStorTemperatureTooLow.name: h3cStorTemperatureTooLow
h3cStorTemperatureTooLow.description: The h3cStorTemperatureTooLow indicates the temperature is lower than the threshold. If the temperature is lower too much than the entity needs, the entity halts now.

h3cExtVoltageLowThresholdNotification.name: h3cExtVoltageLowThresholdNotification
h3cExtVoltageLowThresholdNotification.description: The h3cExtVoltageLowThresholdNotification indicates the Voltage is lower than the low-threshold.

h3cExtVoltageHighThresholdNotification.name: h3cExtVoltageHighThresholdNotification
h3cExtVoltageHighThresholdNotification.description: The h3cExtVoltageHighThresholdNotification indicates the Voltage is lower than the high-threshold.

h3cExtCriticalVoltageLowThresholdNotific.name: h3cExtCriticalVoltageLowThresholdNotification
h3cExtCriticalVoltageLowThresholdNotific.description: The h3cExtCriticalVoltageLowThresholdNotification indicates the Voltage is lower than the critical low threshold.

h3cExtCriticalVoltageHighThresholdNotifi.name: h3cExtCriticalVoltageHighThresholdNotification
h3cExtCriticalVoltageHighThresholdNotifi.description: The h3cExtCriticalVoltageHighThresholdNotification indicates the Voltage is higher than the critical high threshold.

h3cExtVoltageTooLow.name: h3cExtVoltageTooLow
h3cExtVoltageTooLow.description: The h3cExtVoltageTooLowNotification indicates the Voltage is lower than the critical low threshold, and the entity halt now!

h3cExtVoltageTooHigh.name: h3cExtVoltageTooHigh
h3cExtVoltageTooHigh.description: The h3cExtVoltageTooHighNotification indicates the Voltage is higher than the critical high threshold, and the entity halt now!

h3cExtBatteryStateNotification.name: h3cExtBatteryStateNotification
h3cExtBatteryStateNotification.description: The h3cExtBatteryStateNotification indicates the raid battery entity's state changes.

h3cDiskIOErrorNotification.name: h3cDiskIOErrorNotification
h3cDiskIOErrorNotification.description: The h3cDiskIOErrorNotification indicates that a disk occurred I/O error.

h3cRaidCreateNotification.name: h3cRaidCreateNotification
h3cRaidCreateNotification.description: The h3cRaidCreateNotification indicates that a array is created.

h3cRaidDeleteNotification.name: h3cRaidDeleteNotification
h3cRaidDeleteNotification.description: The h3cRaidDeleteStateNotification indicates that a array is deleted.

h3cRaidHideStateNotification.name: h3cRaidHideStateNotification
h3cRaidHideStateNotification.description: The h3cRaidFailedNotification indicates that a array hide or unhide.

h3cRaidRunStateNotification.name: h3cRaidRunStateNotification
h3cRaidRunStateNotification.description: The h3cRaidDegradeNotification indicates that a array state change.

h3cRaidImportNotification.name: h3cRaidImportNotification
h3cRaidImportNotification.description: The h3cRaidFailedNotification indicates that a thrid array is imported.

h3cRaidRebuildStartNotification.name: h3cRaidRebuildStartNotification
h3cRaidRebuildStartNotification.description: The h3cRaidRebuildStartNotification indicates that a array start to rebuild.

h3cRaidRebuildFinishNotification.name: h3cRaidRebuildFinishNotification
h3cRaidRebuildFinishNotification.description: The h3cRaidRebuildStartNotification indicates that a array fininsh rebuild.

h3cRaidRebuildPauseNotification.name: h3cRaidRebuildPauseNotification
h3cRaidRebuildPauseNotification.description: The h3cRaidRebuildPauseNotification indicates that pause a array rebuilding.

h3cRaidRebuildInterruptNotification.name: h3cRaidRebuildInterruptNotification
h3cRaidRebuildInterruptNotification.description: The h3cRaidRebuildInterruptNotification indicates that interrupt a array rebuilding.

h3cSoftwareModuleFailNotification.name: h3cSoftwareModuleFailNotification
h3cSoftwareModuleFailNotification.description: The h3cSoftwareModuleFailNotification indicates that software module(s) fail.

h3cRaidBatteryExpiredNotification.name: h3cRaidBatteryExpiredNotification
h3cRaidBatteryExpiredNotification.description: The h3cRaidBatteryExpiredNotification indicates RAID Battery lifetime had expired.

h3cRaidBatteryWillExpireNotification.name: h3cRaidBatteryWillExpireNotification
h3cRaidBatteryWillExpireNotification.description: The h3cRaidBatteryWillExpireNotification indicates RAID Battery lifetime will expire.

h3cLvOnlineFailNotification.name: h3cLvOnlineFailNotification
h3cLvOnlineFailNotification.description: The h3cLvOnlineFailNotification indicates lv(s) on vd fail to online.

h3cLvOfflineFailNotification.name: h3cLvOfflineFailNotification
h3cLvOfflineFailNotification.description: The h3cLvOfflineFailNotification indicates lv(s) on vd fail to offline.

h3cRaidRunNotification.name: h3cRaidRunNotification
h3cRaidRunNotification.description: The h3cRaidRunNotification indicates that a array is running.

h3cExtVoltageNormal.name: h3cExtVoltageNormal
h3cExtVoltageNormal.description: The h3cStorVoltageRecoveryNotification indicates the Voltage has recovered in reference.

h3cDiskPowerOnNotification.name: h3cDiskPowerOnNotification
h3cDiskPowerOnNotification.description: The h3cDiskPowerOnNotification indicates that a disk is power on.

h3cDiskPowerOffNotification.name: h3cDiskPowerOffNotification
h3cDiskPowerOffNotification.description: The h3cDiskPowerOffNotification indicates that a disk is power off.
